article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Isaiah Thompson scored 26 points as FGCU beat North Florida 79-60 on Wednesday night. Thompson was 9 of 14 shooting (8 for 12 from 3-point range) for the Eagles (13-17, 7-8 Atlantic Sun Conference). Dallion Johnson scored 12 points, going 5 of 9 (2 for 5 from 3-point range). Zach Anderson shot 5 for 11, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. The Ospreys (15-15, 8-7) were led by Chaz Lanier, who posted 14 points and four assists. Jah Nze added 14 points for North Florida. Dorian James also had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
